<paragraph blockId="49.[130,776,215,944]" pageId="49" pageNumber="730">
The?m2 (ANG M-105) has a well-developed central basin. Labial cusps are missing and there are only two lingual cusps as in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hahn &amp; Hahn" authorityYear="1999" box="[197,336,406,432]" class="Mammalia" family="Pinheirodontidae" genus="Bernardodon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" pageId="49" pageNumber="730" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[197,336,406,432]" italics="true" pageId="49" pageNumber="730">Bernardodon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[353,459,406,433]" captionStart="FIG" captionStartId="48.[132,143,1895,1912]" captionTargetBox="[132,1455,215,1848]" captionTargetId="figure-21@48.[132,1455,195,1858]" captionTargetPageId="48" captionText="FIG. 33. — Multituberculate mammal teeth from Angeac-Charente: A, B, left p4 of Pinheirodontidae indet. (ANG M-72) in lingual (A) and labial (B) views; C, D, left P1 of Pinheirodontidae indet. (ANG M-03) in occlusal (C) and distolingual (D) views; E, F, right P2 of Pinheirodontidae indet. (ANG M-06) in occlusal (E) and lingual (F) views; G, H, left P3 of Pinheirodontidae indet. (ANG M-22) in occlusal (G) and lingual (H) views; I, J, left?P4 of Sunnyodon sp. (ANG M-04) in occlusal (I) and labial (J) views; K, L, left?P5 of Multituberculata indet. (ANG M-106) in mesio-occlusal (K) and occluso-labial (L) views; M, N, left?m2 of Pinheirodontidae indet. (ANG M- 105) in occlusal (M) and labial (N) views; O, P, right M2 of Pinheirodontidae indet. (ANG M-32) in occlusal (O) and lingual (P) views. Scale bar: A, B, 1 mm; C, D, 750 µm; E-P, 500 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6902115" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6902115/files/figure.png" pageId="49" pageNumber="730">Fig. 33N</figureCitation>
), whereas there are three in 
<taxonomicName authority="(Hahn &amp; Hahn 1999)" baseAuthorityName="Hahn &amp; Hahn" baseAuthorityYear="1999" box="[134,513,438,465]" class="Mammalia" family="Pinheirodontidae" genus="Pinheirodon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" pageId="49" pageNumber="730" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[134,263,438,464]" italics="true" pageId="49" pageNumber="730">Pinheirodon</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Hahn &amp; Hahn" box="[277,501,438,465]" firstAuthor="Hahn" pageId="49" pageNumber="730" pagination="77 - 222" refId="ref40980" refString="HAHN G. &amp; HAHN R. 1999. - Pinheirodontidae n. fam. (Multituberculata) (Mammalia) aus der tiefen Unter-Kreide Portugals. Palaeontographica Abteilung A: 77 - 222." type="book chapter" year="1999">Hahn &amp; Hahn 1999</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
. Nevertheless, the tooth shape is considerably longer than wide, and precludes assigning it to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hahn &amp; Hahn" authorityYear="1999" box="[227,363,502,528]" class="Mammalia" family="Pinheirodontidae" genus="Bernardodon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" pageId="49" pageNumber="730" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[227,363,502,528]" italics="true" pageId="49" pageNumber="730">Bernardodon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[379,485,502,529]" captionStart="FIG" captionStartId="48.[132,143,1895,1912]" captionTargetBox="[132,1455,215,1848]" captionTargetId="figure-21@48.[132,1455,195,1858]" captionTargetPageId="48" captionText="FIG. 33. — Multituberculate mammal teeth from Angeac-Charente: A, B, left p4 of Pinheirodontidae indet. (ANG M-72) in lingual (A) and labial (B) views; C, D, left P1 of Pinheirodontidae indet. (ANG M-03) in occlusal (C) and distolingual (D) views; E, F, right P2 of Pinheirodontidae indet. (ANG M-06) in occlusal (E) and lingual (F) views; G, H, left P3 of Pinheirodontidae indet. (ANG M-22) in occlusal (G) and lingual (H) views; I, J, left?P4 of Sunnyodon sp. (ANG M-04) in occlusal (I) and labial (J) views; K, L, left?P5 of Multituberculata indet. (ANG M-106) in mesio-occlusal (K) and occluso-labial (L) views; M, N, left?m2 of Pinheirodontidae indet. (ANG M- 105) in occlusal (M) and labial (N) views; O, P, right M2 of Pinheirodontidae indet. (ANG M-32) in occlusal (O) and lingual (P) views. Scale bar: A, B, 1 mm; C, D, 750 µm; E-P, 500 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6902115" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6902115/files/figure.png" pageId="49" pageNumber="730">Fig. 33M</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="49.[130,776,215,944]" pageId="49" pageNumber="730">
The M2 (ANG M-32) shows a prominent anterolingual shelf (
<figureCitation box="[200,302,566,592]" captionStart="FIG" captionStartId="48.[132,143,1895,1912]" captionTargetBox="[132,1455,215,1848]" captionTargetId="figure-21@48.[132,1455,195,1858]" captionTargetPageId="48" captionText="FIG. 33. — Multituberculate mammal teeth from Angeac-Charente: A, B, left p4 of Pinheirodontidae indet. (ANG M-72) in lingual (A) and labial (B) views; C, D, left P1 of Pinheirodontidae indet. (ANG M-03) in occlusal (C) and distolingual (D) views; E, F, right P2 of Pinheirodontidae indet. (ANG M-06) in occlusal (E) and lingual (F) views; G, H, left P3 of Pinheirodontidae indet. (ANG M-22) in occlusal (G) and lingual (H) views; I, J, left?P4 of Sunnyodon sp. (ANG M-04) in occlusal (I) and labial (J) views; K, L, left?P5 of Multituberculata indet. (ANG M-106) in mesio-occlusal (K) and occluso-labial (L) views; M, N, left?m2 of Pinheirodontidae indet. (ANG M- 105) in occlusal (M) and labial (N) views; O, P, right M2 of Pinheirodontidae indet. (ANG M-32) in occlusal (O) and lingual (P) views. Scale bar: A, B, 1 mm; C, D, 750 µm; E-P, 500 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6902115" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6902115/files/figure.png" pageId="49" pageNumber="730">Fig. 33O</figureCitation>
), like that observed in the molars of 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="49" pageNumber="730">Bernarodon</emphasis>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="(Kielan-Jaworowska et al. 2004)" baseAuthorityName="Kielan-Jaworowska" baseAuthorityYear="2004" box="[268,769,598,624]" class="Mammalia" family="Pinheirodontidae" genus="Pinheirodon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" pageId="49" pageNumber="730" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[268,399,598,624]" italics="true" pageId="49" pageNumber="730">Pinheirodon</emphasis>
(Kielan-Jaworowska 
<emphasis box="[637,692,598,624]" italics="true" pageId="49" pageNumber="730">et al.</emphasis>
2004)
</taxonomicName>
. As in the latter two genera there are three lingual cusps, but ANG M-32 differs from other pinheirodontids in lacking the labial cusps (
<figureCitation box="[314,409,693,720]" captionStart="FIG" captionStartId="48.[132,143,1895,1912]" captionTargetBox="[132,1455,215,1848]" captionTargetId="figure-21@48.[132,1455,195,1858]" captionTargetPageId="48" captionText="FIG. 33. — Multituberculate mammal teeth from Angeac-Charente: A, B, left p4 of Pinheirodontidae indet. (ANG M-72) in lingual (A) and labial (B) views; C, D, left P1 of Pinheirodontidae indet. (ANG M-03) in occlusal (C) and distolingual (D) views; E, F, right P2 of Pinheirodontidae indet. (ANG M-06) in occlusal (E) and lingual (F) views; G, H, left P3 of Pinheirodontidae indet. (ANG M-22) in occlusal (G) and lingual (H) views; I, J, left?P4 of Sunnyodon sp. (ANG M-04) in occlusal (I) and labial (J) views; K, L, left?P5 of Multituberculata indet. (ANG M-106) in mesio-occlusal (K) and occluso-labial (L) views; M, N, left?m2 of Pinheirodontidae indet. (ANG M- 105) in occlusal (M) and labial (N) views; O, P, right M2 of Pinheirodontidae indet. (ANG M-32) in occlusal (O) and lingual (P) views. Scale bar: A, B, 1 mm; C, D, 750 µm; E-P, 500 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6902115" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6902115/files/figure.png" pageId="49" pageNumber="730">Fig. 33P</figureCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Hahn &amp; Hahn" box="[421,648,693,720]" firstAuthor="Hahn" pageId="49" pageNumber="730" pagination="77 - 222" refId="ref40980" refString="HAHN G. &amp; HAHN R. 1999. - Pinheirodontidae n. fam. (Multituberculata) (Mammalia) aus der tiefen Unter-Kreide Portugals. Palaeontographica Abteilung A: 77 - 222." type="book chapter" year="1999">Hahn &amp; Hahn 1999</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="49" pageNumber="730" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="49.[130,776,215,944]" pageId="49" pageNumber="730">
The anterior upper premolars P1 (ANG M-03), P2 (ANG M-06) and P3 (ANG M-22) have 3-4 ribbed cusps arranged in two rows like in other “plagiaulacidans” (
<figureCitation box="[635,715,789,815]" captionStart="FIG" captionStartId="48.[132,143,1895,1912]" captionTargetBox="[132,1455,215,1848]" captionTargetId="figure-21@48.[132,1455,195,1858]" captionTargetPageId="48" captionText="FIG. 33. — Multituberculate mammal teeth from Angeac-Charente: A, B, left p4 of Pinheirodontidae indet. (ANG M-72) in lingual (A) and labial (B) views; C, D, left P1 of Pinheirodontidae indet. (ANG M-03) in occlusal (C) and distolingual (D) views; E, F, right P2 of Pinheirodontidae indet. (ANG M-06) in occlusal (E) and lingual (F) views; G, H, left P3 of Pinheirodontidae indet. (ANG M-22) in occlusal (G) and lingual (H) views; I, J, left?P4 of Sunnyodon sp. (ANG M-04) in occlusal (I) and labial (J) views; K, L, left?P5 of Multituberculata indet. (ANG M-106) in mesio-occlusal (K) and occluso-labial (L) views; M, N, left?m2 of Pinheirodontidae indet. (ANG M- 105) in occlusal (M) and labial (N) views; O, P, right M2 of Pinheirodontidae indet. (ANG M-32) in occlusal (O) and lingual (P) views. Scale bar: A, B, 1 mm; C, D, 750 µm; E-P, 500 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6902115" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6902115/files/figure.png" pageId="49" pageNumber="730">Fig. 33</figureCitation>
C-H; Kielan-Jaworowska 
<emphasis box="[344,394,821,847]" italics="true" pageId="49" pageNumber="730">et al.</emphasis>
2004). They are not very diagnostic and only tentatively assigned here to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hahn &amp; Hahn" authorityYear="1999" box="[516,705,853,879]" class="Mammalia" family="Pinheirodontidae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" pageId="49" pageNumber="730" phylum="Chordata" rank="family">Pinheirodontidae</taxonomicName>
, based on their similarities with the pinheirodontid teeth described by 
<bibRefCitation author="Hahn &amp; Hahn" box="[166,403,917,943]" firstAuthor="Hahn" pageId="49" pageNumber="730" pagination="77 - 222" refId="ref40980" refString="HAHN G. &amp; HAHN R. 1999. - Pinheirodontidae n. fam. (Multituberculata) (Mammalia) aus der tiefen Unter-Kreide Portugals. Palaeontographica Abteilung A: 77 - 222." type="book chapter" year="1999">Hahn &amp; Hahn (1999</bibRefCitation>
: fig. 58).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
